<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4106] ExpandoMetaClassCreationHandle does infinite recursion for ExpandoMetaClass</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4106</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in ExpandoMetaClassCreationHandle line 49 (else clause in createNormalMetaClass(Class,MetaClassRegistry)), there is a call&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.create(theClass, registry)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which should be replaced by a call&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;super&lt;/span&gt;.createNormalMetaClass(theClass, registry)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;since, if createNormalMetaClass is invoked, this call came from super.create. Thus the call to super.create(..) creates infinite recursion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This occurs for example when executing code like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;MetaClassCreationHandle handle = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ExpandoMetaClassCreationHandle();
println handle.create(ExpandoMetaClass, GroovySystem.getMetaClassRegistry());
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
